<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <title>Recruit Members - Start a Team</title>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/css/main.css?v=13">
</head>
<body>
  <header></header>
  <main class="start-team-page">
    <div class="container start-team-shell">
      <a href="/start-team" class="btn btn-secondary back-button">&larr; Back to Steps</a>
      <p class="step-label">Step 1 of 6</p>
      <h1>Find a Sponsor Organization</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Your FTC team needs a sponsoring school, club, community group, or nonprofit to register and compete.</p>
      <section class="content-section">
        <p>Your team needs sponsors to compete because robotics costs money — parts, field rental, travel, and event fees add up fast. A fiscal sponsor or nonprofit partner helps your team operate like a nonprofit and accept donations.</p>

        <div class="sponsor-info-grid">
          <div>
            <h3>Why sponsors matter</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Enable fundraising and donation support through nonprofit channels</li>
              <li>Provide official fiscal sponsorship and financial oversight</li>
              <li>Offer access to grants, equipment, and community resources</li>
              <li>Help your team qualify for school, club, or nonprofit programs</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Action:</strong> Talk to a school administrator, club leader, or nonprofit coordinator about sponsoring your team, or consider a fiscal sponsor that can make your team nonprofit-friendly.</p>
            <p>Also plan for parent fundraising, community drives, and local support if you are starting without a school sponsor.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="step-detail-logos">
            <img src="/assets/img/HACK%20CLUB.jpg" alt="Hack Club logo">
            <img src="/assets/img/HACK+.jpg" alt="Hack+ logo">
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
      <div class="step-actions">
        <a href="/start-team-step2" class="btn btn-primary">Next: Connect with FIRST →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <script src="/assets/js/main.js?v=8"></script>
</body>
</html>
